item.title: India's Champions Trophy squad announcement postponed, BCCI requests ICC for extension, new date is…: Report - Hindustan Times
item.description:
BCCI Postpones India's Champions Trophy Squad Announcement

Date: January 11, 2025 Source: Hindustan Times

The BCCI has requested an extension from the ICC for announcing India's squad for the Champions Trophy, which was initially scheduled for January 12, in order to finalize their selection.

  • The announcement delay stems from the BCCI's request for more time to finalize the squad.
  • Teams were expected to name provisional squads five weeks before the tournament, but the BCCI is citing recent commitments in Australia.
  • The new date for announcing the squad is likely January 19, one month before the tournament starts.
  • The provisional squad is expected to see mostly the same players as those in the ODI series against England.
  • India's T20I squad against England is also expected to be announced shortly.
  • A review meeting will involve BCCI officials, captain Rohit Sharma, and coach Gautam Gambhir.
The BCCI aims to finalize the squad while addressing recent performance issues after a disappointing series against Australia.

The BCCI's careful planning aims to ensure that the squad is well-prepared following recent overseas matches, indicating a strategic approach to the upcoming Champions Trophy.

item.title: AAP MLA Gurpreet Gogi shoots himself accidentally, declared dead - The Hindu
item.description:
AAP MLA Gurpreet Gogi Accidentally Shoots Himself and is Declared Dead

Publication Date: January 11, 2025 Source: The Hindu

Aam Aadmi Party (AAP) MLA Gurpreet Gogi has been pronounced dead after accidentally shooting himself, resulting in serious head injuries. The incident took place around midnight.

  • Gurpreet Gogi sustained bullet injuries to his head and was declared dead at the hospital.
  • The Deputy Commissioner of Police stated that the shooting was accidental as per family accounts.
  • The cause of death will be confirmed once the post-mortem report is available.
  • Gogi, who joined AAP in 2022, previously defeated a two-time Congress MLA during the Ludhiana assembly elections.
“The incident happened around midnight, and he was declared dead when he was brought to the DMC hospital...” - DCP Jaskaran Singh

Further investigations into the incident are currently underway.

AAP Punjab MLA Gurpreet Gogi Bassi Found Dead from Gunshot Wound

Date: Jan 11, 2025

Source: Hindustan Times

AAP MLA Gurpreet Gogi Bassi from Ludhiana West was declared dead due to a gunshot wound late Friday night, with the cause of death still under investigation.

  • Gurpreet Gogi Bassi was declared dead on arrival at Dayanand Medical College and Hospital.
  • An autopsy will confirm if his death was due to suicide or accidental firing.
  • Bassi had recently participated in community activities, including a cleanliness drive.
  • He joined AAP in 2022, defeating a two-time MLA in the elections.
“The cause of death is yet to be determined,” said commissioner Kuldeep Singh Chahal.

This tragic incident raises concerns about the safety of politicians and the circumstances surrounding such incidents in Punjab.

item.title: Cambodian man dies from H5N1 avian flu, possibly after eating sick chickens - University of Minnesota Twin Cities
item.description:
Cambodian Man Dies from H5N1 Avian Flu After Possible Exposure to Sick Chickens

Date: January 10, 2025

Source: Avian Flu Diary

A 28-year-old man from Kampong Cham province in Cambodia has died from an H5N1 avian flu infection after being exposed to and possibly consuming sick chickens. This is the 19th human case of H5N1 identified in Cambodia since early 2023.

  • The patient exhibited symptoms including fever, difficulty breathing, cough, and fatigue.
  • His family raises chickens, and he cooked sick chickens for food.
  • This incident follows a previous fatal case in September 2024 involving a teenage girl.
  • Cambodian officials have not yet released details on the specific clade involved in this case.
The detection occurred during a surge in H5N1 cases in both humans and poultry.

The recent cases underline the ongoing threat of avian influenza in the region and the importance of monitoring and preventive measures.

item.title: World's 1st wooden satellite deploys from ISS to demonstrate cleaner spacecraft tech (photo) - Space.com
item.description:
World's 1st wooden satellite deploys from ISS to demonstrate cleaner spacecraft tech (photo)

Publication Date: January 7, 2024 | Source: Space.com

An experimental satellite made of wood, named LignoSat, has been launched from the International Space Station (ISS) to test the durability of sustainable materials in space.

  • LignoSat is developed by Kyoto University and Sumitomo Forestry, designed to test wood’s ability to withstand space conditions.
  • The mission may lead to a new generation of environmentally friendly satellites.
  • It will remain in space for approximately six months, monitoring its wooden structure against temperature extremes and radiation.
  • NASA is analyzing the satellite's interaction with the geomagnetic field during its mission.
“If we can prove our first wooden satellite works, we want to pitch it to Elon Musk's SpaceX.” - Retired Japanese astronaut Takao Doi

This pioneering effort could potentially reshape the future of satellite construction to mitigate the environmental impact of satellite reentries.

item.title: ‘Despicable charade, no merit’ says Donald Trump after unconditional discharge in hush money case - Hindustan Times
item.description:
Trump Claims 'Witch Hunt' After Being Discharged in Hush Money Case

Date: Jan 11, 2025

Source: Hindustan Times

Donald Trump expressed his outrage over the Biden-Harris administration's actions against him, labeling it a 'witch hunt' after receiving an unconditional discharge in his hush money trial despite 34 felony counts.

  • Trump was convicted of 34 felony counts but received an unconditional discharge, avoiding jail time and fines.
  • He condemned the charges as baseless and claimed they were a result of political oppression.
  • Trump announced plans to appeal the case, which he called a 'hoax' and a 'scam'.
  • The case involved a $130,000 payment to an adult film star to prevent an affair from being disclosed during his presidential campaign.
“That result alone proves that, as all Legal Scholars and Experts have said, THERE IS NO CASE, THERE WAS NEVER A CASE, and this whole Scam fully deserves to be DISMISSED,” said Trump.

This case highlights the ongoing legal battles Trump faces and has reignited his claims of being unjustly targeted by political opponents.
